The fallacy of false piety‚ intending to honour Christ's discipleS, is met by the fact that Christ upon earth refused all such honour. Friars excuse their high living by the good they do3 such an excuse would be just as available for every possible excess. To excuse such scandals is to be worse than Iscariot; he at least affected to think of the poor, when he reproached Magdalen: they do not.
